# amielke-overlay

Gentoo overlay with additional ebuilds for software not available in the main Gentoo repository.

## Installation

### Recommended method

Install `eselect-repository` if it is not already installed:

```bash
emerge --ask app-eselect/eselect-repository

Add the overlay:

eselect repository add amielke-overlay git https://github.com/amielke/amielke-overlay.git

Sync the repository:

emaint sync -r amielke-overlay

Manual method

If you prefer manual repository configuration, create:

/etc/portage/repos.conf/amielke-overlay.conf

with the following content:

[amielke-overlay]
location = /var/db/repos/amielke-overlay
sync-type = git
sync-uri = https://github.com/amielke/amielke-overlay.git
auto-sync = yes
masters = gentoo
priority = 50

Then sync the repository:

emaint sync -r amielke-overlay

Usage

After syncing, packages from the overlay can be installed with Portage as usual:

emerge --ask category/package

Scope

This overlay contains selected ebuilds and related packaging work for software outside the main Gentoo tree.

Depending on the package, this may include:

    desktop applications

    gaming-related tools

    binary packages

    proprietary software

    testing or work-in-progress ebuilds

Notes

    This overlay is distributed directly through its Git repository.

    It does not need to be listed in the official Gentoo repository list in order to work.

    Packages in this overlay may change over time.

    Some ebuilds may still be experimental or under active testing.

    Some packages may rely on upstream binary releases or proprietary sources.

    Always review ebuilds before using them on important or production systems.

Bug reports and contributions

If you find a problem with an ebuild, please open an issue in this repository.

Useful bug reports should ideally include:

    package name and version

    complete emerge error output

    relevant system information

    any local changes made to the ebuild

Pull requests and improvements are welcome.
Disclaimer

This overlay is provided as-is.

Use it at your own risk, especially when installing binary or proprietary software.
License

Unless otherwise noted, ebuilds in this repository follow normal Gentoo overlay conventions.

Individual packages may have their own upstream licenses. See the corresponding ebuilds and installed license files for details.


